From the hint, we immediately see that

\begin{align*}
1! + 2! + 3! + 4! + 5! + ... + 100! &\equiv 1! + 2! + 3! + 4! \mod{10}\\
&\equiv 1 + 4 + 6 + 24 \mod{10}\\
&\equiv 5 \mod{10}
\end{align*}

